8. Mechanism-oriented Evidence Chain
from data linkage to endpoint mechanism hypothesis
This section defines how the tabular outputs of N1a–N8 are linked to support a sample-level lineage-structure mechanism endpoint. The mechanism addressed here is restricted to the within-sample lineage-structure mechanism: stable coexistence, mixed input, technical artifact, or unresolved. It is not a manufacturing mechanism, regulatory mechanism, market mechanism, brand-level inference, species-label certification, or absolute composition estimate.
Layer 1. 输入与质量边界（N1a–N2c）
Input TSV ->
raw_fastq_inventory.tsv, raw_fastq_md5.tsv, read_structure_check.tsv, manifest_schema_audit.tsv, manifest_ITS1.tsv, manifest_ITS2.tsv, sample_groups.tsv, control_manifest.tsv, aux_control_manifest.tsv, qc_summary_by_sample_marker.tsv, rarefaction_by_sample_marker.tsv, denoise_stats_by_marker.tsv, ITS1_feature_table.tsv, ITS2_feature_table.tsv.
Computation action ->
Public FASTQ files are audited for file integrity, read structure, manifest consistency, sample-marker-replicate identity, control stratification, sequencing quality, depth sufficiency, denoising status, and marker-specific feature generation.
Output TSV ->
exclusion_log.tsv, qc_summary_by_sample_marker.tsv, rarefaction_by_sample_marker.tsv, denoise_stats_by_marker.tsv, feature_generation_log.tsv, ITS1_feature_table.tsv, ITS2_feature_table.tsv.
Mechanism question answerable ->
This layer can answer whether each public ITS1/ITS2 FASTQ unit is computationally eligible to contribute evidence to a sample-level lineage-structure mechanism endpoint.
Question not answerable ->
This layer cannot determine stable coexistence, mixed input, technical artifact, or unresolved status. It also cannot interpret read_count as absolute abundance, biomass, or actual mixture ratio.
Layer 2. 谱系证据形成（N3a–N5b）
Input TSV ->
ITS1_feature_table.tsv, ITS2_feature_table.tsv, taxonomy_assignment_ITS1.tsv, taxonomy_assignment_ITS2.tsv, annotation_confidence.tsv, annotation_conflict_log.tsv, unassigned_features.tsv, lineage_support_by_marker.tsv, cross_marker_support_matrix.tsv, marker_discordance_log.tsv, replicate_support_matrix.tsv, control_overlap_by_lineage.tsv.
Computation action ->
Marker-specific features are converted into lineage keys with annotation confidence, rank compatibility, conflict status, unassigned status, ITS1/ITS2 concordance, technical replicate stability, and stratified control-level overlap.
Output TSV ->
taxonomy_assignment_ITS1.tsv, taxonomy_assignment_ITS2.tsv, annotation_confidence.tsv, annotation_conflict_log.tsv, unassigned_features.tsv, lineage_support_by_marker.tsv, cross_marker_support_matrix.tsv, marker_discordance_log.tsv, replicate_support_matrix.tsv, control_overlap_by_lineage.tsv, risk_traceability_audit.tsv.
Mechanism question answerable ->
This layer can answer whether a candidate lineage is supported by one or both markers, whether the signal is replicate-stable, whether annotation is compatible across markers, and whether the signal overlaps with a stratified control level.
Question not answerable ->
This layer cannot issue a final endpoint call. Single-marker support, annotation confidence, replicate behavior, or control overlap alone cannot be used to conclude stable coexistence, mixed input, or technical artifact.
Layer 3. 支持/风险/缺口整合（N6a–N6c）
Input TSV ->
cross_marker_support_matrix.tsv, replicate_support_matrix.tsv, annotation_confidence.tsv, control_overlap_by_lineage.tsv, risk_traceability_audit.tsv, annotation_conflict_log.tsv, marker_discordance_log.tsv, feature_generation_log.tsv.
Computation action ->
Positive support evidence, risk evidence, and evidence gaps are merged into a frozen endpoint-ready evidence vector. Control-level information is retained as stratified risk annotation only, no cross-level subtraction.
Output TSV ->
support_evidence_matrix.tsv, risk_evidence_matrix.tsv, evidence_gap_catalog.tsv, endpoint_ready_evidence.tsv.
Mechanism question answerable ->
This layer can answer whether a sample has sufficient integrated evidence to proceed to endpoint calling, whether support evidence dominates, whether risk evidence dominates, or whether evidence gaps require unresolved handling.
Question not answerable ->
M6/N6c is the endpoint-ready evidence integration layer and outputs only endpoint_ready_evidence.tsv; it does not output endpoint calls.
Layer 4. 机制型终点判定（N7）
Input TSV ->
endpoint_ready_evidence.tsv, endpoint_decision_rulebook.tsv.
Computation action ->
The frozen endpoint-ready evidence vector is evaluated by the decision rulebook to assign one sample-level lineage-structure mechanism endpoint and one certainty class.
Output TSV ->
sample_endpoint_call.tsv, unresolved_cases.tsv.
Mechanism question answerable ->
This layer answers the study endpoint: whether the public ITS1/ITS2 raw FASTQ evidence supports classifying each sample as stable coexistence, mixed input, technical artifact, or unresolved, together with certainty_class.
Question not answerable ->
N7/M7 cannot infer absolute abundance, biomass, actual ingredient ratio, manufacturing history, regulatory status, market prevalence, brand performance, or species-label authenticity.
Layer 5. 机制解释边界（N8）
Input TSV ->
sample_endpoint_call.tsv, unresolved_cases.tsv, evidence_gap_catalog.tsv, mechanism_interpretation_notes.tsv.
Computation action ->
N7/M7 endpoint calls and evidence gaps are summarized for post-terminal interpretation, limitation statements, and evidence-bound mechanism discussion.
Output TSV ->
mechanism_interpretation_notes.tsv.
Mechanism question answerable ->
This layer can explain why a sample-level lineage-structure mechanism endpoint was limited, downgraded, or left unresolved based on evidence boundaries.
Question not answerable ->
N8/M8 is post-terminal discussion-only and cannot modify any N7/M7 endpoint call. It cannot create new endpoint categories, upgrade or downgrade certainty, reinterpret N7/M7, or fill endpoint evidence gaps with speculative mechanisms.
