9. Study Type and Endpoint Positioning
This study is not a pure methodology paper. It is a question-driven study that applies established ITS1/ITS2 metabarcoding workflows to evaluate whether public raw FASTQ data can support a sample-level lineage-structure mechanism endpoint in commercial herbal-material samples.
The metabarcoding workflow is used as an analytical toolchain, whereas the research endpoint is the mechanism-oriented evidence classification of within-sample lineage structure. The endpoint is not a benchmark of method performance itself, not a brand comparison, not a regulatory assessment, not a market-level extrapolation, not a species-label certification framework, and not an absolute composition estimate.
N7/M7 is the sole endpoint call layer and outputs only four endpoint classes: stable coexistence, mixed input, technical artifact, or unresolved, together with certainty_class.
N8/M8 is a post-terminal discussion-only layer that may explain evidence boundaries but cannot feed back to modify, upgrade, downgrade, or reinterpret any N7/M7 endpoint call.
M6/N6c is the endpoint-ready evidence integration layer and outputs only endpoint_ready_evidence.tsv; it does not output endpoint calls.
read_count is used only for within-sample support ranking and evidence integration, not for absolute abundance, biomass, or actual mixture ratio.
